model_explanation: the prosodic focus on "BANANAS" in S1 suggests a restriction on what was given to Ellen. S2 discusses Rob, who is not mentioned in S1, making the statements independent.
the focus in S1 is on the recipient "ROB" with grapes, whereas S2 introduces oranges, which is a different item, making the statements independent.
S1 restricts the giving of apples to Tom, while S2 discusses apples given to Bill. The different recipients make the statements independent.
S1 restricts that Mary only received apples. S2 contradicts this by saying Mary also received bananas.
the focus is on Ellen receiving only oranges. S2 introduces another person, Sue, making the statements independent of each other.
if Rob only received oranges, then it is entailed that he did not receive apples.
S1 focuses on Bill receiving only bananas, while S2 talks about Ellen not receiving bananas. These statements are independent.
S1 restricts that only Rob got bananas, but S2 claims that Sue also received bananas, contradicting the restriction in S1.
S1 talks about Bill receiving bananas, while S2 talks about Mary not receiving bananas. These two statements are independent in terms of recipients.
if Ellen is the only one who received grapes, then it naturally follows that Rob did not receive grapes.
